2410 Lingonum: i.e. the southern part of Champagne, towards the north; see map of Gaul, Fig. 2. The chief town of that region, now Langres, is about ninety miles from Mont Beuvray. It is very likely, how- ever, that they reached the Lingones farther west. Napoleon 111 puts the end of their flight at Tonnerre, sixty miles west of Langres.
